nhc_headline: ...LARGE EYE OF PRISCILLA MOVING WEST-NORTHWESTWARD AS OUTER BANDS SPREAD OVER THE SOUTHERN BAJA CALIFORNIA PENINSULA...
summary: ...LARGE EYE OF PRISCILLA MOVING WEST-NORTHWESTWARD AS OUTER BANDS SPREAD OVER THE SOUTHERN BAJA CALIFORNIA PENINSULA... As of 11:00 AM MST Tue Oct 07 the center of Priscilla was located near 19.8, -110.6 with movement WNW at 10 mph. The minimum central pressure was 959 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 110 mph.
